fields.physical_description:
Sepia photographic print of landscape proportions, mounted in a folder of buff card & paper (the front cover printed with the photographer's name & address on a scroll). The image shows Doris Winifred Youens and Laurence Elmes, on the occasion of their wedding, with the best man & three bridesmaids.  In the centre of the group are Laurence (in a morning suit with a lily-of-the-valley buttonhole) & Doris (in a short
white two-tiered frock with veil, floral tiara, pearls, & (incorrectly held) shower bouquet of roses & sprengeri fern; Laurence's best man (in a similar outfit to his) stands to his right.  The two adult bridesmaids (the one on the right is the bride's sister, Vera Maud Youens) are seated one at each side of the group, & wear identical outfits: scoop necked short dresses (with tiered scallop-edged skirts and long sleeves), gloves, picture hats, & strap shoes, with shower bouquets of daffodils, smilax & asparagus fern.  The child bridesmaid, seated in front of the bride & groom, wears a short dress (with tiered skirt & short sleeves), gloves, a Dutch winged cap, ankle socks and strap shoes, & holds a posy of flowers.  The setting consists of a fur rug, brocaded curtains, and a potted aspidistra on a what-not.
fields.marks: A Portrait by Edwards & Co, 206, High Street N., East Ham, E6
fields.object: Photographic print mounted in card & paper folder
fields.history_note:
References: 


The print shows the donor's maternal aunt, Doris
Winifred Youens (born 13/05/1901) on the occasion of her
marriage to Laurence Elmes.  The donor's mother, Vera
Maud Kempson (born 16/09/1899), was one of the two adult
bridesmaids
